{
  "_meta": {
    "version": 1,
    "account_currency": "USD",
    "assumption_set": "dukascopy_public_baseline_approx",
    "notes": [
      "These settings are calibrated to public Dukascopy trading-condition pages where possible, with approximate proxies where Dukascopy exposes policy but not a directly scrapeable per-instrument table.",
      "FX commission uses Dukascopy's public self-trader low-tier schedule: USD 35 per 1 million USD traded, converted to 0.35 bps per side.",
      "Precious metals, crypto and index CFD commission uses Dukascopy's public low-tier schedule: USD 52.5 per 1 million USD traded, converted to 0.525 bps per side.",
      "Single-stock CFD commission is approximated at 1.0 bps per side, which is close to Dukascopy's public US-stock schedule near the current AAPL/NVDA/TSLA price range after applying the USD 0.02 per share cap logic.",
      "FX weekday leverage is modeled at 1:100, Gold at 1:50, Silver at 1:30, crypto at 1:5, index CFDs at 1:20 and single-stock CFDs at 1:10, in line with Dukascopy public pages.",
      "Maintenance margin is approximated as half the initial margin ratio to mimic Dukascopy's margin-cut threshold near use-of-leverage 200%.",
      "Overnight rates are annualized proxies for Dukascopy-style rolling spot financing, not exact daily swap points from the live rollover widget.",
      "USDCNH uses CNH as the PnL currency and can be proxied by USDCNY for FX conversion when CNH data is unavailable."
    ]
  },
